  "text": "where EF is the enrichment factor of target element X, (X/Fe)aerosol is the concentration ratio of X to Fe in the aerosol samples, and (X/Fe)crust is the average concentration ratio of X to Fe in crustal dust. If EF is 1 to 5, the element X can be considered to originate mainly from soil; if EF > 5, the element X mainly originated from human activities [CITATION_1] .",
